## Performance & Accessibility Strategy
- Use `useReducedMotion` hook from Framer Motion to disable continuous or heavy translations for users who prefer reduced motion.
- Keep looping animations (like status dots) extremely lightweight (opacity/scale only).
- Animate `transform` and `opacity` properties to avoid paint/layout reflow costs.
- Ensure all animations run at 60fps on mobile by stripping out complex SVG lines on smaller screens if they cause lag.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Dev Tests
- Run `npm run dev` and navigate to `http://localhost:3000/engine`.
- Check browser console for hydration errors or Framer Motion warnings.

### Manual Verification
- Open the page and verify the Hero visual clearly shows the transformation timeline.
- Scroll down the page and verify that `whileInView` animations trigger reliably.
- Hover over interactive elements (cards, icons, inputs) to ensure premium elasticity without cartoonish bounciness.
- Test in mobile window size to confirm motion is simplified to key transitions.
